HTML Interview question and answer
-----------------------------------
Que 1) What are HTML Elements?
Que 2) What is a Tag?

Que 1) What are HTML Elements?
-------------------------------
HTML elements are the building blocks of a web page. 🧱
Every web page is made using many HTML elements.
An HTML element has 3 parts:
Opening Tag – tells the browser where the element starts
Content – the text or data inside the element
Closing Tag – tells the browser where the element ends
Example
<p>Interview Happy</p>
Explanation:
<p> → Opening tag
Interview Happy → Content
</p> → Closing tag
So the complete element is:
<p>Interview Happy</p>
Que 2) What is a Tag?
------------------------
A Tag is only the keyword inside < > brackets.
Example:
<p>      → Opening Tag
</p>     → Closing Tag
Tags do not contain content.
They only mark the start or end of an element.
3️⃣ Difference Between Element and Tag
Tag	Element
Part of HTML code	Complete structure
Written inside < >	Includes tag + content
Example: <p>	Example: <p>Hello</p>
Simple Example
Tag:
<p>
</p>
Element:
<p>Hello</p>
✅ One-line interview answer
HTML elements are the building blocks of web pages and consist of a start tag, content, and an end tag. A tag is
only the opening or closing part of an element.
